The Centre for Development of Advanced Computing (CDAC) is committed to protecting your privacy, while delivering the software that brings you the features provided in the e-Sushrut UP HMIS (DGME) Mobile App. This privacy statement governs your use of the e-Sushrut UP HMIS (DGME) Mobile App.
</li>

<li>
This app provides features for patients and doctors of UPDGME Hospitals which use the Hospital Management Information System (HMIS) of the Centre for Development of Advanced Computing (CDAC), Noida.
</li>
</ul>

<div class="section-title">COLLECTION AND USE OF YOUR INFORMATION</div>

<ul>
<li>
The e-Sushrut UP HMIS (DGME) Mobile App does not collect or transmit to CDAC personally identifiable information or require the use of logins, passwords, etc. generated in the mobile app. The app uses the camera and record audio permissions to enable video calling between patients and doctors during teleconsultation workflows. The option to revoke these permissions can be set from the app settings options on the mobile device.
</li>
</ul>

<div class="section-title">SECURITY OF YOUR INFORMATION</div>

<ul>
<li>
CDAC respects and protects the privacy of the individuals who use HMIS Mobile App services and is committed to helping protect the security of your information. The information captured by the app is not shared with any third party.
</li>
</ul>

